大多数的LGBT组织都有[[异性恋|异性恋]]或[[顺性别|顺性别]]人士参与；其他人也鼓励他们加入其中。[[同志與非同志聯盟|同直联盟]]是一个由学生运营的社团，它将LGBT人群与非LGBT人群聚集在一起并创建一个行动平台，并以此对抗[[同性恋恐惧|同性恋恐惧]]和[[跨性别恐惧症|跨性别恐惧]]。<ref>{{cite web |title=Build the GSA Movement |url=https://gsanetwork.org/build-the-gsa-movement/ |publisher=GSANetwork |accessdate=2019-05-08 |archive-date=2021-03-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210321054207/https://gsanetwork.org/build-the-gsa-movement/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Support Youth Organizing |url=https://gsanetwork.org/support-youth-organizing/ |publisher=GSANetwork |accessdate=2019-05-08 |archive-date=2021-04-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210420200204/https://gsanetwork.org/support-youth-organizing/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> 还有一些社团致力于将LGBT社群联合起来与直同志合作。成立于1973年的[[PFLAG|PFLAG]]（同性恋父母、家人与朋友组织）是最早的直同志组织，它由“直同志运动”之母{{Link-en|珍妮·曼福德|Jeanne Manford}}创立。PFLAG的总部位于美国，它将LGBTQ+人士与他们的父母、家人及朋友联合起来，为LGBTQ+人群争取完全的公民权利与法律平等。2007年，该组织启动了一个新的项目——“直人挺平权（{{lang|en|Straight for Equality}}）”。这个项目将帮助更多的直同志参与到LGBTQ+人群在工作场所、医疗保健及宗教社区获得平等的运动。<ref>{{cite web |title=About Straight for Equality |url=http://www.straightforequality.org/about |publisher=[[PFLAG|PFLAG]] |accessdate=2019-05-08 |archive-date=2021-02-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225184826/http://www.straightforequality.org/about |dead-url=no }}</ref> {{Link-en|GLBTQ法律权益与捍卫者|GLBTQ Legal Advocates & Defenders}}则是另一个持该相同举动的直同志组织。<ref>{{cite web |title=What We Do |url=https://www.glad.org/our-impact/ |publisher=GLBTQ Legal Advocates & Defenders |accessdate=2019-05-08 |archive-date=2021-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121231556/https://www.glad.org/our-impact/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

一些LGBT伴侣的孩子也是直同志，例如{{Link-en|扎克·沃尔斯|Zach Wahls}}。他是一对女同性恋者的儿子，尽管他对LBGT社群有其他的看法。<ref>{{cite web |author1=Phil Reese |title=That kid from YouTube |url=https://www.washingtonblade.com/2012/05/23/that-kid-from-youtube-grows-up/ |publisher=Washington Blade |accessdate=2019-05-08 |archive-date=2020-10-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201015171013/https://www.washingtonblade.com/2012/05/23/that-kid-from-youtube-grows-up/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

